main event: An extremely bright orange object was observed moving up and down, back and forth, and hovering over the Nome-Teller Road in Alaska on September 29, 1967.
interesting points: The object moved up and down and back and forth, mostly hovering and looking or observing.
At times, light was given off from the sides and down the sides from the top up.
The object finally disappeared behind the hills.
The sighting lasted for about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
There were no photographs taken of the object.
